1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:01,810
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,810 --> 00:00:03,310
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,310 --> 00:00:05,080
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,610 --> 00:00:08,050
(Episode 26)

5
00:00:08,950 --> 00:00:12,350
It looks like our key witness
has arrived.

6
00:00:43,580 --> 00:00:46,580
Are things finally about
to go up in flames?

7
00:00:49,150 --> 00:00:51,660
Park Tae Ho, Choi Yu Na,

8
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:55,360
and everyone at the Adele Group.

9
00:00:57,300 --> 00:01:00,830
I hope they all push each other...

10
00:01:01,670 --> 00:01:03,400
into a fiery pit of despair.

11
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:14,180
This is the man
from the false accusation video.

12
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:19,080
Who gave you Chloe's design book
and put you up to this?

13
00:01:21,290 --> 00:01:23,960
It was her. Choi Yu Na.

14
00:01:26,060 --> 00:01:28,890
Are you insane?
What nonsense are you spouting?

15
00:01:29,890 --> 00:01:32,860
That's not all, is it?
To keep you quiet,

16
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:35,700
someone kidnapped
and kept you locked up, didn't they?

17
00:01:37,340 --> 00:01:41,370
That crazy woman locked me up
and made me film a confession video.

18
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:45,240
What's more, she even tried
to traffic me overseas!

19
00:01:46,950 --> 00:01:47,950
Shut your mouth.

20
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:50,980
Mom, please, that's enough.

21
00:01:51,850 --> 00:01:55,020
Why are you making a scene too?
What did I even do?

22
00:01:56,150 --> 00:01:58,320
I got involved with Ms. Choi
for nothing,

23
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:00,490
and now I'm stuck in this mess
with no shares to show for it.

24
00:02:01,390 --> 00:02:04,730
I'm the one
who's been wronged the most here.

25
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:06,360
What are you talking about?

26
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:08,270
This could've been handled quietly,

27
00:02:08,270 --> 00:02:10,500
but you insisted on
dealing with it yourself.

28
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:13,040
You even blackmailed me
for my shares.

29
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:16,540
So if anyone's a victim here,
it's me.

30
00:02:17,610 --> 00:02:19,510
- What?
- Ms. Oh, please!

31
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:22,580
- You know I'm right.
- Choi Yu Na!

32
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:37,960
This is quite the show.

33
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:42,470
In my own home?
Right in front of me? The nerve!

34
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:45,900
The audacity of all of you.

35
00:02:46,740 --> 00:02:47,910
Manager Kang!

36
00:02:49,870 --> 00:02:52,540
- Yes?
- Get this trash out of here first.

37
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,680
Yes, sir.

38
00:02:55,710 --> 00:02:58,780
Where are you taking me?
This wasn't part of the deal!

39
00:02:59,550 --> 00:03:01,220
- Father.
- Quiet!

40
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:04,460
All of you, shut up and follow me.

41
00:03:33,590 --> 00:03:36,020
Choi Yu Na, how dare...

42
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:40,220
you lie to me
and tarnish Adele Group's name?

43
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:44,400
- That's...
- Shut it.

44
00:03:49,370 --> 00:03:51,370
The Adele Group chairman's wife...

45
00:03:51,370 --> 00:03:53,170
resorting to kidnapping
and imprisonment?

46
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:59,280
If this gets out,
the entire company could collapse.

47
00:03:59,810 --> 00:04:02,480
- I'm telling you, I've been framed.
- Will you be quiet?

48
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:12,360
And you, Kim Myung Hui.

49
00:04:14,090 --> 00:04:18,530
You found him and dragged him here
without reporting to me first?

50
00:04:20,230 --> 00:04:22,170
Every single one of you...

51
00:04:23,230 --> 00:04:26,300
has defied me, Park Tae Ho?

52
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:32,380
In any case,
the truth of this incident is out.

53
00:04:32,740 --> 00:04:35,010
We must call the police
and take legal measures...

54
00:04:35,010 --> 00:04:36,250
Enough.

55
00:04:36,550 --> 00:04:39,580
Involving the law
will only complicate things.

56
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:43,050
Are you really going
to leave it at that?

57
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:46,460
We already have his confession
on video.

58
00:04:47,090 --> 00:04:50,030
The cleanest way to handle this
is to pay him to turn himself in.

59
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:52,060
I don't want to hear
another word about it.

60
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:58,640
Absolutely not.

61
00:04:59,140 --> 00:05:02,740
They must be duly punished
for what they've done.

62
00:05:04,740 --> 00:05:06,280
Didn't you hear the chairman?

63
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:10,150
He told you not to question him.
Why are you still talking?

64
00:05:11,980 --> 00:05:13,250
Please reconsider.

65
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:15,950
You're not fixing anything.
You're just covering it up.

66
00:05:16,890 --> 00:05:18,220
That's right.

67
00:05:19,890 --> 00:05:21,260
Our Adele Group...

68
00:05:23,660 --> 00:05:27,270
This is my family's dirty laundry.
Of course I'm going to hide it.

69
00:05:27,870 --> 00:05:31,740
They will be punished,
but on my terms.

70
00:05:33,270 --> 00:05:34,570
Manager Kang.

71
00:05:40,450 --> 00:05:41,710
Get these things...

72
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:45,550
out of my sight right now.

73
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:48,390
Make sure they never set foot
in this house again!

74
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,020
- Yes, sir.
- What?

75
00:05:50,020 --> 00:05:52,620
Honey.
How dare you lay a hand on me?

76
00:05:53,190 --> 00:05:56,660
How could you do this
after saying you'd keep it a secret?

77
00:05:56,730 --> 00:05:57,730
Honey!

78
00:05:58,100 --> 00:06:00,100
Hyun Jun!

79
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:03,070
Let go of me. Sir!

80
00:06:03,130 --> 00:06:05,040
You can't do this to me.

81
00:06:05,300 --> 00:06:07,140
- You should leave.
- Let go of me.

82
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:09,370
Just a minute. Let go!

83
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:15,150
That should be enough, right?

84
00:06:16,550 --> 00:06:17,550
No, it's not.

85
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:20,990
What they did deserves
legal punishment.

86
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,160
What about you?

87
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:27,660
Do you feel the same way?

88
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:30,600
I...

89
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:37,740
I think this is enough.

90
00:06:40,070 --> 00:06:41,110
Park Hyun Jun.

91
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:43,040
The point is, it's been handled.

92
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:46,840
I only helped to stop my mom, not...

93
00:06:51,580 --> 00:06:53,050
I don't want to see her in prison.

94
00:06:57,960 --> 00:07:00,420
This is as far as you two go.

95
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:04,660
In return,
I'll call off Min Jun's wedding.

96
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,980
Do you think
you can get away with this?

97
00:07:27,050 --> 00:07:30,120
For the chairman and Adele Group,
I suggest you control yourself.

98
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:33,220
I'm not finished talking
to the chairman!

99
00:07:33,360 --> 00:07:36,230
Stop making a scene
and just leave quietly.

100
00:07:36,730 --> 00:07:38,460
You're embarrassing us
in front of the whole neighborhood.

101
00:07:42,970 --> 00:07:46,040
How dare you! Why you...

102
00:07:50,010 --> 00:07:53,640
I'll make them pay for this.
Unbelievable!

103
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:02,950
Kim Myung Hui, you.

104
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:05,390
It'll be hard
to come back from this.

105
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:07,690
Says who?

106
00:08:07,890 --> 00:08:10,390
The chairman would never abandon me.

107
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:14,330
Isn't this the first time
he's thrown you out completely...

108
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,870
instead of moving you to the annex?

109
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:19,670
It looks to me like the chairman's
already had a change of heart.

110
00:08:26,710 --> 00:08:28,480
I warned you a long time ago.

111
00:08:29,410 --> 00:08:32,080
Not to let your greed consume you
and turn you into a monster.

112
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:35,550
You said you were willing
to become a monster,

113
00:08:37,090 --> 00:08:38,520
and this is what it's gotten you.

114
00:08:43,030 --> 00:08:44,230
Both of you.

115
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:46,700
Take a good, hard look
at what you've become.

116
00:08:49,270 --> 00:08:51,570
Look at how low and pathetic
you've become.

117
00:08:52,470 --> 00:08:54,010
It's a shame I'm the only one
who gets to see it.

118
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:57,340
Then again,

119
00:08:58,180 --> 00:09:00,710
for treating a human life
so cheaply,

120
00:09:01,110 --> 00:09:02,580
this is nowhere near enough.

121
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:08,320
If you ever treat another human life
so lightly again,

122
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:12,860
you'll pay for it with your life.

123
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:14,560
Mark my words.

124
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:19,600
Hey. You!

125
00:09:21,570 --> 00:09:22,700
This isn't over.

126
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,300
I'll kill you, Kim Myung Hui!

127
00:09:29,370 --> 00:09:30,370
Darn it.

128
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:32,780
You!

129
00:09:34,350 --> 00:09:35,350
Hey!

130
00:09:35,910 --> 00:09:38,580
Choi Yu Na was kicked out
without putting up a fight.

131
00:09:39,650 --> 00:09:42,290
Looks like she doesn't have the guts
to stand up to Park Tae Ho.

132
00:09:42,550 --> 00:09:44,260
Hey, open this door!

133
00:09:44,260 --> 00:09:46,420
I'll have to back her
into a tighter corner.

134
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:48,230
Put on your shoes.

135
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:51,630
Yes, get it ready for me.

136
00:10:05,310 --> 00:10:06,310
Manager Kang.

137
00:10:07,450 --> 00:10:09,050
What did you do with that man?

138
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:13,020
I sent him home safely.
You don't need to worry.

139
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:14,790
You probably cut a deal with him...

140
00:10:14,790 --> 00:10:16,420
on the condition
that he turns himself in...

141
00:10:17,020 --> 00:10:18,220
and keeps his mouth shut.

142
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:22,390
I was merely following
the chairman's orders.

143
00:10:22,890 --> 00:10:23,890
If you'll excuse me.

144
00:10:41,510 --> 00:10:43,010
Chairman Park!

145
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:47,020
- Sir!
- Chairman Park.

146
00:10:50,290 --> 00:10:52,220
Chairman Park!

147
00:10:54,990 --> 00:10:56,060
Chloe?

148
00:10:57,030 --> 00:10:58,660
What are you doing here?

149
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:01,570
Chloe?

150
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,000
Yes, you.

151
00:11:06,140 --> 00:11:08,010
Chloe or whatever your name is,
it was you, wasn't it?

152
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,440
How dare you steal my phone
and cause this whole mess?

153
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:13,340
Then...

154
00:11:13,910 --> 00:11:15,710
the one
who set this whole thing up...

155
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:20,320
What is your problem?

156
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:21,990
Why do you keep getting in my way?

157
00:11:22,450 --> 00:11:26,190
My plans are ruined thanks to you.
It's all your fault!

158
00:11:29,890 --> 00:11:31,160
If you feel wronged,

159
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:33,300
why don't we go to the police?

160
00:11:34,570 --> 00:11:36,970
We'll see whose life was ruined...

161
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:38,440
and stolen.

162
00:11:39,540 --> 00:11:42,770
Let's settle this fair and square
before the law.

163
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:50,080
Stop with the cheap shots
with a rock in your hand.

164
00:11:53,180 --> 00:11:54,190
What?

165
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:56,090
A rock?

166
00:11:58,590 --> 00:11:59,960
What do you mean by that?

167
00:12:03,430 --> 00:12:05,030
The law? Please.

168
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:09,830
Listen.
The world runs on power, not laws.

169
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:14,640
With Adele Group behind me,
can some paltry law touch me?

170
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:17,410
And yet...

171
00:12:18,110 --> 00:12:20,280
here you are,
kicked out just like this.

172
00:12:21,650 --> 00:12:23,610
- Why, you...
- Ms. Oh!

173
00:12:28,990 --> 00:12:32,360
Hyun Jun, what's with you today?

174
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:33,990
What's wrong with you, Mom?

175
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:37,600
How can you be so shameless?

176
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:40,200
What did you just say?

177
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:41,970
I found out everything.

178
00:12:43,030 --> 00:12:45,840
You showed me your true colors
and how low you can go.

179
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,540
Aren't you ashamed of yourself?

180
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:50,880
Don't you feel guilty at all
for disappointing your son?

181
00:12:53,710 --> 00:12:56,850
Do you know why I was glad each time
you were kicked out to the annex?

182
00:12:57,250 --> 00:12:59,250
I was so ashamed...

183
00:12:59,250 --> 00:13:01,990
that I put on a brave face
and brushed it off as nothing.

184
00:13:02,150 --> 00:13:04,720
You know why I helped Park Min Jun?

185
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:08,930
Because if I didn't,
I'd end up just like you.

186
00:13:11,860 --> 00:13:15,170
If I got kicked out in disgrace,
I would be no different from you.

187
00:13:16,670 --> 00:13:17,670
Hyun...

188
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:19,340
Hyun Jun.

189
00:13:21,610 --> 00:13:23,270
Still, I was worried about you.

190
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:28,380
But now, I can't even bring myself
to worry anymore.

191
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,480
Because I'm too ashamed.

192
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:45,660
This is so annoying.

193
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:47,630
Of all things, why a rock?

194
00:13:48,970 --> 00:13:50,100
This is driving me nuts.

195
00:13:57,810 --> 00:13:59,110
Park Hyun Jun!

196
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:09,820
Darn.

197
00:14:10,520 --> 00:14:12,590
If I'd known,
I would've kept my mouth shut.

198
00:14:15,590 --> 00:14:16,930
This is so embarrassing.

199
00:14:18,630 --> 00:14:20,230
Don't think that.

200
00:14:22,070 --> 00:14:23,170
If anything,

201
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:25,670
you made a very difficult choice.

202
00:14:28,470 --> 00:14:29,540
Your mother...

203
00:14:30,010 --> 00:14:32,240
will probably be investigated
by the police now.

204
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:38,120
Come on.

205
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:41,450
Let's stop the serious talk.
For now, let's just...

206
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:43,850
smile.

207
00:14:48,690 --> 00:14:49,690
I made you smile.

208
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:53,200
Is this the Chloe effect?

209
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:55,830
Now that we're smiling
together like this,

210
00:14:57,470 --> 00:14:59,040
it feels like
the whole atmosphere has changed.

211
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:03,370
It's like we've gone back
to a time...

212
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:06,610
when we didn't have a care
in the world.

213
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:10,380
You had a time like that?

214
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:13,950
Back in college.

215
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:17,420
Those were the simplest
and most fun times.

216
00:15:18,490 --> 00:15:19,490
What about you, Chloe?

217
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:24,660
For me...

218
00:15:26,530 --> 00:15:29,000
I think it was back then as well.

219
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:33,970
I didn't have a care in the world...

220
00:15:37,310 --> 00:15:39,180
and was just happy.

221
00:15:56,160 --> 00:15:58,600
I know it was urgent,
so I let it happen,

222
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:02,070
but it was too dangerous for you
to follow him with just Chloe.

223
00:16:07,570 --> 00:16:10,410
Are you disappointed
with how things turned out?

224
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:13,280
What about you, Mother?

225
00:16:13,810 --> 00:16:15,680
Do you agree with Father's decision?

226
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:21,520
In the 30 years I've spent surviving
in the Adele family,

227
00:16:23,150 --> 00:16:25,490
I disagreed with more
than I agreed with.

228
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:30,260
If I had fought back
every single time,

229
00:16:30,690 --> 00:16:32,600
I wouldn't have gotten anywhere.

230
00:16:33,830 --> 00:16:36,870
If I had to object,
I had to have several plans ready.

231
00:16:37,070 --> 00:16:38,500
And if I couldn't object,

232
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:41,840
I had to figure out
what I could gain from it.

233
00:16:42,270 --> 00:16:43,470
In this case,

234
00:16:43,910 --> 00:16:46,710
if it can finally resolve
your wedding issues,

235
00:16:47,580 --> 00:16:51,280
I think we should go along
with the chairman's decision.

236
00:16:52,950 --> 00:16:55,490
Are you having a hard time
accepting it?

237
00:16:57,420 --> 00:16:59,490
It's disappointing,
but I can accept it.

238
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:01,330
When I think about Hyun Jun,

239
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:03,830
I can sort of understand why.

240
00:17:05,030 --> 00:17:07,560
- But...
- You're worried about Chloe.

241
00:17:08,470 --> 00:17:10,400
She's very direct and honest.

242
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:14,040
She'll have a hard time accepting
that the truth was covered up.

243
00:17:15,070 --> 00:17:16,940
Chloe's name has been cleared,

244
00:17:17,210 --> 00:17:18,910
and your wedding has been canceled.

245
00:17:19,110 --> 00:17:21,180
Now that even Hyun Jun
feels relieved,

246
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:24,280
I'm sure Chloe will understand
if we explain the situation to her.

247
00:17:26,320 --> 00:17:27,650
Try not to worry too much.

248
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,310
What? Hold on.

249
00:17:50,340 --> 00:17:51,540
Who are you, people?

250
00:17:53,340 --> 00:17:54,380
Darn it.

251
00:17:54,850 --> 00:17:55,910
You punk!

252
00:17:58,180 --> 00:17:59,220
You punk.

253
00:18:01,950 --> 00:18:02,950
You!

254
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:04,560
Min Jun!

255
00:18:05,220 --> 00:18:06,790
I know what I heard.

256
00:18:08,890 --> 00:18:10,330
Why would she call my name
like that?

257
00:18:16,830 --> 00:18:17,970
Darn.

258
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:21,910
What is Yu Na doing out this late?

259
00:18:21,910 --> 00:18:23,570
I can't even get a hold of her.

260
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:24,680
For goodness' sake.

261
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:27,480
Did she get caught
sneaking the jacket out...

262
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:30,110
and get taken away by the police?

263
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:34,490
Please. If she'd been arrested,
we would've gotten a call by now.

264
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:36,490
Besides, that girl takes after me.

265
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:38,460
She wouldn't have gotten caught
so easily.

266
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:41,360
- Oh my, she's back.
- Goodness.

267
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:42,530
Oh my gosh, Yu Na.

268
00:18:42,530 --> 00:18:45,430
What on earth happened to you?

269
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:48,100
Don't tell me
the chairman knows everything.

270
00:18:48,970 --> 00:18:51,800
Wait, will the police
be taking you in?

271
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,640
The police? Don't be ridiculous.

272
00:18:54,140 --> 00:18:57,170
What the... What's going on?

273
00:18:58,280 --> 00:18:59,710
The chairman said...

274
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:03,280
he'd handle this quietly.

275
00:19:03,910 --> 00:19:06,180
We'll be back in his good graces
once he calms down a bit.

276
00:19:06,180 --> 00:19:07,420
For crying out loud.

277
00:19:07,420 --> 00:19:08,650
Really? Is that true?

278
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:11,460
Goodness. True or not,

279
00:19:11,660 --> 00:19:14,120
what's she doing here
with that smug look on her face,

280
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:15,660
barging into our house?

281
00:19:16,860 --> 00:19:18,530
She got kicked out just like me.

282
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:20,300
- What?
- What?

283
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:21,930
What was that?

284
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:25,370
Let's get one thing straight.

285
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:28,510
You were kicked out.
I'm just lying low for a while.

286
00:19:29,940 --> 00:19:31,240
Unbelievable.

287
00:19:32,410 --> 00:19:34,240
My word.

288
00:19:34,310 --> 00:19:36,650
What on earth is going on?

289
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:41,620
Jung Ran, please calm down
and hear me out.

290
00:19:41,690 --> 00:19:45,760
Calm or not, you're dead meat today.
You hear me?

291
00:19:45,820 --> 00:19:48,990
You botched that one little job
and got me kicked out of the house!

292
00:19:49,060 --> 00:19:51,430
- I swear I did my best!
- Your best?

293
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,130
What's all this?

294
00:19:53,730 --> 00:19:55,230
Why does it have to be my room
of all places?

295
00:19:55,230 --> 00:19:56,230
Darn.

296
00:19:56,230 --> 00:19:58,140
- You, get over here.
- Goodness, Yu Na.

297
00:19:58,200 --> 00:20:00,170
- That woman!
- Get over here.

298
00:20:04,940 --> 00:20:07,440
- Goodness.
- I swear, you...

299
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,450
Jung Ran, please stop.

300
00:20:09,780 --> 00:20:13,450
- Unbelievable!
- What are these fools doing?

301
00:20:15,050 --> 00:20:16,450
Oh dear.

302
00:20:16,450 --> 00:20:18,060
Jung Ran!

303
00:20:30,030 --> 00:20:31,570
Things got weird.

304
00:20:33,170 --> 00:20:36,340
I thought we solved the problem
as a team,

305
00:20:38,010 --> 00:20:40,410
so why do I feel like
I did something wrong?

306
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:49,250
Hey,

307
00:20:50,650 --> 00:20:52,020
About yesterday...

308
00:20:52,020 --> 00:20:53,060
Forget it.

309
00:20:53,590 --> 00:20:55,630
- I get where you're coming from.
- Really?

310
00:20:56,630 --> 00:20:57,830
Are you sure you understand?

311
00:20:59,100 --> 00:21:00,960
Your face says you don't.

312
00:21:02,270 --> 00:21:04,430
Why are you looking at me
like I'm the bad guy?

313
00:21:04,530 --> 00:21:05,900
It's not like that.

314
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,010
It's just...

315
00:21:08,740 --> 00:21:11,540
I'm not sure if we should
just sweep this under the rug.

316
00:21:12,140 --> 00:21:13,140
I see.

317
00:21:13,410 --> 00:21:14,410
Are you upset...

318
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:16,650
that my mom didn't go to jail?

319
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:18,420
Don't twist my words.

320
00:21:21,180 --> 00:21:23,520
I'm just worried about
how Chloe will handle all this...

321
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:25,290
since she's the victim.

322
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:29,890
I had other things on my mind
about Chloe, too.

323
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:32,930
I'm not holding anything
against you.

324
00:21:36,430 --> 00:21:39,070
So he thinks I just wrapped this up
without caring about Chloe?

325
00:21:42,210 --> 00:21:43,740
I don't want to get defensive,

326
00:21:44,980 --> 00:21:46,610
but why am I so bothered by this?

327
00:21:48,610 --> 00:21:51,850
So, is what Ms. Choi did
just going to be covered up?

328
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:56,750
The accuser turned himself in,
so the case will be closed soon.

329
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:59,720
Chairman Park's people will probably
use money to make it go away.

330
00:22:00,260 --> 00:22:02,290
Oh Jung Ran gets kicked out
of the house, and that's it?

331
00:22:02,390 --> 00:22:04,900
If it gets out
that the chairman's wife...

332
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:06,800
kidnapped and imprisoned someone,

333
00:22:07,230 --> 00:22:08,730
the stock price would tank,

334
00:22:09,030 --> 00:22:11,740
and there would be major backlash
against the owner's family.

335
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:16,540
The chairman would've wanted
to keep it as quiet as possible.

336
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:20,280
Still, she committed a crime.
Can we just let it end like this?

337
00:22:21,080 --> 00:22:23,610
Of course,
I can't just leave it at that.

338
00:22:24,150 --> 00:22:26,120
She may have avoided
legal punishment,

339
00:22:26,380 --> 00:22:28,390
but I won't let her make
an easy comeback,

340
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:31,120
even if it means
exposing her other crimes.

341
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:34,790
How are things with the gallery?

342
00:22:35,490 --> 00:22:37,030
It's a total fortress.

343
00:22:37,460 --> 00:22:39,700
It's Park Tae Ho's channel...

344
00:22:39,700 --> 00:22:41,900
for laundering funds
and exchanging bribes.

345
00:22:42,830 --> 00:22:44,900
No evidence is getting out.

346
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:48,810
We need some kind of smoking gun.

347
00:22:49,270 --> 00:22:52,210
It'd be great
if we found a ledger or something.

348
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:54,910
A smoking gun?

349
00:23:04,690 --> 00:23:07,460
You can't just go rummaging
through someone else's closet.

350
00:23:07,560 --> 00:23:09,790
You're being rude
and making a scene.

351
00:23:10,890 --> 00:23:13,630
What are you going to do
if you get kicked out of here too?

352
00:23:14,260 --> 00:23:15,800
You can't even get a hotel room...

353
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:17,100
because all your cards
have been cut off.

354
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:20,540
That's exactly why I need to find
a way back in, and fast.

355
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:22,940
To do that, I need fresh clothes.

356
00:23:24,470 --> 00:23:25,910
Is there even a way for you
to get back in?

357
00:23:26,710 --> 00:23:31,080
Just lie low
until Chairman Park forgives you.

358
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:34,620
If I'm going to wait,
I should do it inside the house.

359
00:23:34,890 --> 00:23:37,150
If I'm stuck out here too long,
that witch Kim Myung Hui...

360
00:23:37,790 --> 00:23:40,460
will take over the house
and the company.

361
00:23:42,090 --> 00:23:44,190
I need to get back fast,
even if I have to play...

362
00:23:44,290 --> 00:23:45,330
my trump card early.

363
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:48,870
The secret entrance you dug
for the house is still there, right?

364
00:23:49,170 --> 00:23:51,700
What? You're planning to sneak in?

365
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:54,600
If you get caught,
it will be chaos again.

366
00:23:54,740 --> 00:23:56,140
Then I just won't get caught.

367
00:23:56,970 --> 00:23:58,010
Lead the way. Now.

368
00:24:06,650 --> 00:24:09,590
Knowing Oh Jung Ran,
she won't just sit back and wait.

369
00:24:10,050 --> 00:24:13,020
She's never been kicked out before,
so she must be getting antsy.

370
00:24:14,390 --> 00:24:17,290
Have someone tail Oh Jung Ran
and keep an eye on her.

371
00:24:18,060 --> 00:24:19,730
Got it. I'll get right on it.

372
00:24:20,730 --> 00:24:22,730
We must be careful not to get caught
by Chairman Park.

373
00:24:23,470 --> 00:24:26,570
If he thinks we're disobeying him
and causing problems,

374
00:24:27,340 --> 00:24:28,870
he'll show us no mercy.

375
00:24:29,970 --> 00:24:33,540
Now that he's personally stepped in
to protect Adele,

376
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:36,810
he's even more cold-blooded
and terrifying.

377
00:24:41,250 --> 00:24:42,920
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

378
00:24:42,990 --> 00:24:44,290
What about that punk?

379
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,790
Don't worry about him, sir.

380
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:49,630
He won't cause any trouble
for the group.

381
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:52,000
That's a given.

382
00:24:53,260 --> 00:24:55,570
I don't want any loose ends either.

383
00:24:56,270 --> 00:24:59,040
I've been by your side
for over 20 years, sir.

384
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,300
I'm more than capable...

385
00:25:02,110 --> 00:25:03,470
of ensuring his silence.

386
00:25:04,170 --> 00:25:05,180
Really?

387
00:25:07,610 --> 00:25:08,710
I like the sound of that.

388
00:25:10,010 --> 00:25:11,010
One moment, sir.

389
00:25:15,150 --> 00:25:16,190
Right.

390
00:25:16,820 --> 00:25:17,890
What?

391
00:25:26,160 --> 00:25:28,030
Has Chloe not come in yet?

392
00:25:29,100 --> 00:25:31,640
Contact Chloe
and set up a lunch meeting.

393
00:25:32,070 --> 00:25:33,300
She's the one this all happened to.

394
00:25:33,800 --> 00:25:35,870
She'll have a hard time accepting
that it's over just like that.

395
00:25:36,370 --> 00:25:38,580
I need to explain the situation
and ask for her understanding.

396
00:25:39,880 --> 00:25:40,880
Got it.

397
00:25:47,620 --> 00:25:50,120
Everyone looks busy this morning.

398
00:25:50,650 --> 00:25:53,020
An article just came out,

399
00:25:53,460 --> 00:25:55,430
and we're not sure
what to do about it.

400
00:25:55,530 --> 00:25:58,060
It's an article
about the design book theft.

401
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:00,930
- Can I see it?
- Sure.

402
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:03,200
Here you go.

403
00:26:04,530 --> 00:26:07,670
(Major Company Covers Up
Internal Design Book Theft)

404
00:26:19,150 --> 00:26:20,620
An article about the theft?

405
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:23,390
Yes. I'm the one
who leaked the story.

406
00:26:24,490 --> 00:26:27,420
I might even do an interview next.

407
00:26:30,490 --> 00:26:33,900
This matter is now closed.

408
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:35,900
Right.

409
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:39,200
I'm fully aware
of how you handled it.

410
00:26:40,370 --> 00:26:44,140
But as the victim,
I can't accept that.

411
00:26:45,180 --> 00:26:48,040
How am I supposed to work
with Choi Yu Na,

412
00:26:48,380 --> 00:26:49,510
who came after me?

413
00:26:50,750 --> 00:26:51,780
Sir.

414
00:26:56,190 --> 00:26:58,490
You really have no idea
how it feels...

415
00:26:59,990 --> 00:27:01,320
to be wronged like that.

416
00:27:04,830 --> 00:27:07,830
You could've done the interview
from the beginning,

417
00:27:08,130 --> 00:27:10,100
but you leaked the story,
and now you're threatening me.

418
00:27:12,570 --> 00:27:14,070
What do you want?

419
00:27:14,670 --> 00:27:16,970
Fire Ms. Choi.

420
00:27:17,740 --> 00:27:19,580
Do that,
and I'll reconsider the interview.

421
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:22,750
As for what your wife did...

422
00:27:26,320 --> 00:27:28,950
I'll even try to keep that a secret.

423
00:27:41,630 --> 00:27:44,770
(Team Leader, Choi Yu Na)

424
00:27:50,610 --> 00:27:52,880
Ms. Choi getting fired means...

425
00:27:54,410 --> 00:27:55,850
the article was true, right?

426
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:58,210
Everything points to it.

427
00:27:58,550 --> 00:28:00,280
She was the one
who stole the design book.

428
00:28:02,990 --> 00:28:04,150
Are you okay?

429
00:28:04,620 --> 00:28:05,920
I can't believe
our colleague did that.

430
00:28:06,260 --> 00:28:08,630
Her being fired is one thing.
You should also press charges.

431
00:28:17,330 --> 00:28:18,330
Choi Yu Na.

432
00:28:20,740 --> 00:28:21,840
You actually came to work?

433
00:28:22,810 --> 00:28:24,310
After everything
that happened yesterday?

434
00:28:27,940 --> 00:28:30,450
The chairman is going
to handle this quietly.

435
00:28:31,250 --> 00:28:32,980
Doesn't that mean
nothing ever happened?

436
00:28:35,950 --> 00:28:37,920
Just because I got kicked out
of your house...

437
00:28:38,290 --> 00:28:41,160
doesn't mean I was fired
from the company.

438
00:28:48,300 --> 00:28:49,300
Ms. Choi.

439
00:28:52,870 --> 00:28:54,040
You've been terminated.

440
00:28:57,040 --> 00:28:58,040
Terminated?

441
00:28:58,310 --> 00:29:00,840
These are the chairman's orders.
Please leave.

442
00:29:02,510 --> 00:29:03,510
The chairman?

443
00:29:05,750 --> 00:29:08,180
I must see the chairman now.
Get out of my way.

444
00:29:10,220 --> 00:29:13,560
Let me go. Get off me! Let go!

445
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:17,590
I said let go. Get off me!

446
00:29:20,900 --> 00:29:24,170
I bet it's finally sinking in now.

447
00:29:25,270 --> 00:29:26,940
The fear of being thrown away
by Chairman Park Tae Ho...

448
00:29:27,470 --> 00:29:30,210
and abandoned by Adele.

449
00:29:32,340 --> 00:29:35,310
Good. With that fear and anger,

450
00:29:35,750 --> 00:29:37,850
fight back
against Chairman Park Tae Ho.

451
00:29:38,980 --> 00:29:42,050
Make him think that he has...

452
00:29:42,620 --> 00:29:43,850
to kill you.

453
00:29:50,630 --> 00:29:51,660
Leaking the story to the press...

454
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:54,000
and getting Ms. Choi fired.

455
00:29:55,770 --> 00:29:56,770
That was all you, wasn't it?

456
00:29:58,070 --> 00:30:00,870
Is this your way
of punishing Ms. Choi?

457
00:30:02,970 --> 00:30:06,280
Everyone at Adele
only looks out for themselves.

458
00:30:07,210 --> 00:30:10,780
The case was closed without even asking
what the victim wanted.

459
00:30:11,980 --> 00:30:14,420
So I had to take matters
into my own hands.

460
00:30:15,950 --> 00:30:18,050
I was just about
to explain the situation...

461
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:19,820
and ask for your understanding.

462
00:30:19,820 --> 00:30:21,760
You mean make excuses, right?

463
00:30:23,990 --> 00:30:27,100
Save the excuses you're making
just to ease...

464
00:30:27,630 --> 00:30:29,130
your own conscience.

465
00:30:31,530 --> 00:30:32,540
Excuse me.

466
00:30:42,150 --> 00:30:44,250
(Secretary Jung)

467
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:47,780
Oh Jung Ran is making her move.

468
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:09,070
Oh, man.

469
00:31:09,740 --> 00:31:12,080
Gosh, my leg. Darn, my back.

470
00:31:13,840 --> 00:31:16,650
You call this a secret passage?
It's barely a mousehole!

471
00:31:17,310 --> 00:31:19,180
It was so tight, I almost lost it.

472
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:22,520
Any bigger,
and it's basically the front door.

473
00:31:23,720 --> 00:31:24,790
Hyun Jun used this...

474
00:31:24,790 --> 00:31:28,630
to sneak out and go clubbing
without his dad finding out.

475
00:31:29,630 --> 00:31:32,700
Come on, stop whining
and just get the thing already.

476
00:31:33,630 --> 00:31:36,030
Shut your trap and keep watch.

477
00:31:38,900 --> 00:31:39,900
Careful.

478
00:31:40,470 --> 00:31:41,470
Go that way.

479
00:31:53,820 --> 00:31:56,250
Nice.
I'll grab what I need and slip out.

480
00:32:02,130 --> 00:32:03,130
Where is it?

481
00:32:13,240 --> 00:32:14,700
What are you doing here?

482
00:32:14,800 --> 00:32:15,810
What?

483
00:32:20,540 --> 00:32:21,780
Let go, darn it.

484
00:32:52,810 --> 00:32:55,880
(Pearl in Red)

485
00:32:55,980 --> 00:32:58,610
You got me caught by Kim Myung Hui!
I nearly had a heart attack.

486
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:00,650
- What were you in there to grab?
- A secret ledger?

487
00:33:00,650 --> 00:33:01,750
A secret ledger?

488
00:33:01,750 --> 00:33:03,020
There's no way...

489
00:33:03,020 --> 00:33:05,290
that pathetic book proves
I forced you to do anything.

490
00:33:05,360 --> 00:33:08,830
If this becomes a problem,
you'll pay the price, not me.

491
00:33:08,890 --> 00:33:10,530
- Honey.
- Choi Yu Na!

492
00:33:10,530 --> 00:33:12,900
You got me fired, didn't you?

493
00:33:13,030 --> 00:33:15,030
Just accept
that you've been tossed aside.

494
00:33:15,130 --> 00:33:18,670
Just you wait.
I'll prove I can't be cast aside.

495
00:33:18,770 --> 00:33:20,500
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
